definition.value: A monocarboxylic acid anion resulting from the removal of a proton from the carboxy group of 6-phospho-D-gluconic acid.
An ADP-aldose having ribose as the aldose fragment.
A gamma-amino acid that is butanoic acid with the amino substituent located at C-4.
A dihydroxyanthraquinone that is anthracene-9,10-dione in which the two hydroxy groups are located at positions 1 and 2.
